'''''Soergelia''''' is a genus of extinct [[Ovibovini|ovibovine]] [[Caprinae|caprine]] that was common across [[Europe]] and [[Asia]] in the [[Pleistocene]] epoch.<ref>http://fossilworks.org/?page=paleodb</ref><ref name="Palombo et al., 2010" /><ref name="Martinez-Navarro et al., 2012" />

Species include:

* {{extinct}}''[[Soergelia brigittae]]'' {{small|Kostopolous, 1997}}<ref name="Kostopoulos, 1997" />
* {{extinct}}''[[Soergelia minor]]'' {{small|Moyà-Solà, 1987}}
* {{extinct}}''[[Soergelia intermedia]]'' {{small|Crégut-Bonnoure & Dimitrijević, 2006}}<ref name="Cregut-Bonnoure et al., 2006" />
* {{extinct}}''[[Soergelia elisabethae]]'' {{small|Schaub, 1951}}<ref name="Schaub, 1951" />
* {{extinct}}''[[Soergelia mayfieldi]]'' {{small|(Troxell, 1915)}}<ref name="Troxell, 1915" /><ref>{{GBIF |id=121495810 |taxon=''Soergelia mayfieldi'' (Troxell, 1915) |accessdate=30 August 2017 }}</ref>

